<item>
            <title>[MATH-483] FastMath does not handle all special cases correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-483</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FastMath has some issues with special cases such as +0.0 and -0.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the double cases so far found:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;abs(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
signum(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
asin(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
atan(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
log10(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;-Infinity&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;NaN&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
toDegrees(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
toRadians(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
ulp(-Infinity) expected:&amp;lt;Infinity&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;NaN&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And float cases:&lt;br/&gt;
abs(-0.0) expected:&amp;lt;0.0&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;-0.0&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
